{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "971ec8b9-ff16-4f21-a5c5-3f169935d907",
    "name": "Cinema Ticket Booking API",
    "description": "Import-ready HTTP collection for the Cinema Ticket Booking API.\n\nSetup\n1. Start the stack with `docker compose up --build`.\n2. Sign in through the frontend and copy the Firebase ID token into the collection variable `firebase_token`. The token is intentionally not committed.\n3. Run the folders in order. Catalogue requests select a movie, future showtime, and available seat automatically. Booking requests then save `hold_id` and `booking_id`.\n4. The Admin folder requires the signed-in email to be listed in `ADMIN_EMAILS`.\n\nDirect Google OAuth can also use Postman's cookie jar. Leave `firebase_token` empty, complete the browser redirect, and call `Current user` to capture the session-bound `csrf_token`.\n\nWebSocket requests use a separate Postman multi-protocol collection. Open `{{websocket_url}}/showtimes/{{showtime_id}}` manually to inspect seat snapshots and events.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
